> Randomly generate points in a squre
> count how many fall inside the quarter circle
> use the ration to estimate Pi

Pi ~= 4 x (points in circle) / (Total points)


    OpenMP:

gcc -fopenmp -o monte_openmp monte_carlo_openmp.c -lm

    MPI:

mpicc -o monte_mpi monte_carlo_mpi.c

    Hybrid (MPI + OpenMP):

mpicc -fopenmp -o monte_hybrid monte_carlo_hybrid.c -lm


Run the Executables

    OpenMP (e.g., using 4 threads):

export OMP_NUM_THREADS=4
./monte_openmp #<nu of point>

    MPI (e.g., using 4 processes):

mpirun -np 4 ./monte_mpi

    Hybrid (e.g., 2 MPI processes Ã— 2 threads):
    
export OMP_NUM_THREADS=2
mpirun -np 2 ./monte_hybrid

serial
gcc -o monte_serial monte_carlo_serial.c

Run and Time:

time ./monte_serial


